report.title: Rather Boring
report.author: Anon
report.bodytext: Anon acquired 5 hits of supposed lsd. /n /n Abt. 9:30a.m.: Drop 1 /n /n Abt. 11a.m.: A not quite euphoric high begins to build, w/ slight anxiety /n /n Abt. 12p.m.: Rising high stalls and almost disappears until 1p.m. /n /n Abt.2p.m.: Heavy 'stoned' feeling sets in w/o usual psychedelic character. More a narcotic, opiate-like stoned, only slightly trippy. Not dysphoric but not esp. 'happy' and lightheaded like LSD is (for anon.). /n /n Abt. 3 p.m.: Peak. Kind of an LSA/alcohol type inebriation, w/o LSA nausea. Neither deeply meditative or fun, rather boring really. No visuals aside from subtle color variations and waving (but not exactly) effect on objects. /n /n 3-5 p.m.: Pretty even plateau. Gradual drop off until sometime after 12 a.m. Slept poorly. /n /n Conclusion: CERTAINLY not LSD. A wild guess it was some RC, a phen maybe, tho. based on reading only, anon has no exp. aside from mesc. The blotter was unperforated and an off white color...anon pitched remaining blotter.
